        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 5:31AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 530 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Amarillo, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 70 and 77.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
